{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1df93c2b-8975-4b3e-acb1-e89bea1e9f79","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything resolves. If you reference any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` NuGet packages, bump those to their `11.x` versions as well.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b0ff4066-fa11-4157-ad38-0a515e65de17","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've already told me exactly what files need changing.","outputTokens":278},"id":"896e5cbb-0ebc-4078-9a4f-869ec92c3b1c","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:00:51.281Z","parentId":"5e6ca28b-2789-40a8-9430-4c9e3a6dcef9"}
